  "body": "### Description\n\nKubernetes considers setting `resources.requests` and `resources.limits` a good practice. I did not find any documentation for Quarkus application recommendations.\r\n\r\nWith a JVM based image going as little as little `resource.limits.cpu=0.2` will actually result in various exceptions of level __WARN__ that scheduling a thread took longer than the default configuration of 1s.\r\n\r\nRefs:\r\n[Kubernetes -> Addon Resources](https://kubernetes.io/docs/setup/best-practices/cluster-large/#addon-resources)\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
